# Go Anchor ↔ Rust Anchor Parity

When implementing or reviewing Go Solana Anchor code, verify it matches the official [Rust Anchor](https://www.anchor-lang.com/) behavior. Use this mapping as the source of truth.

## Core Concepts

| Rust Anchor | Go Equivalent | Notes |
|-------------|---------------|-------|
| `declare_id!("...")` | `var ProgramID = solana.MustPublicKeyFromBase58("...")` | Program address constant |
| `#[program]` module | N/A (program-side) | Instruction dispatch; Go focuses on client |
| `Context<AccountsStruct>` | `anchor.Context` with `Accounts`, `ProgramID`, `Bumps` | First arg to instruction handlers |
| `#[account]` struct | Struct with Borsh tags + 8-byte discriminator | Account data layout |

## Account Types

| Rust | Go | Validation |
|------|----|-----------|
| `Account<'info, T>` | `*Account[T]` | Owner check, discriminator, deserialize |
| `AccountLoader<'info, T>` | `*AccountLoader[T]` | Zero-copy for large accounts |
| `UncheckedAccount<'info>` | `*UncheckedAccount` | No validation |
| `Signer<'info>` | `Signer` | Transaction signer check |
| `Program<'info, System>` | `*Program` | Executable, matches program ID |
| `SystemAccount<'info>` | `*SystemAccount` | Owner == System Program |

## Account Constraints (Client-Side Mapping)

When building instructions or validating accounts, ensure Go logic mirrors these constraints:

| Rust `#[account(...)]` | Go validation / behavior |
|------------------------|--------------------------|
| `init` | Account created via CPI; space allocated; payer set |
| `init_if_needed` | Same as init but no-op if account exists |
| `mut` | Account included as writable in instruction |
| `signer` | Signer in transaction |
| `seeds = [...], bump` | Derive PDA; validate address matches |
| `has_one = field` | Account.field == other_account.key |
| `address = expr` | account.Key == expr |
| `owner = expr` | account.Owner == expr |
| `close = target` | Lamports sent to target on close |
| `constraint = expr` | Custom boolean check |
| `realloc` | Resize account; payer for delta |
| `token::mint`, `token::authority` | SPL Token account constraints |
| `associated_token::*` | ATA validation |

## Discriminators

- **Account**: `sha256("account:" + type_name)[0:8]`
- **Instruction**: `sha256("global:" + instruction_name)[0:8]`
- **Event**: `sha256("event:" + event_name)[0:8]`

Go must use the same byte order and hashing as Rust.

## Serialization

- Use **Borsh** for account data, instruction args, events.
- Layout must match Rust `borsh::BorshSerialize` / `BorshDeserialize`.
- Anchor adds 8-byte discriminator before account/event payload.

## IDL Alignment

- Parse IDL v0.30+ (`address`, `metadata`, `instructions`, `accounts`, `types`, `events`, `errors`).
- Instruction `discriminator` is 8-byte array; map to instruction selector.
- Account `discriminator` used for validation and decoding.

## Parity Checklist for New Code

1. [ ] Discriminators match Anchor (account, instruction, event)
2. [ ] Borsh layout matches Rust for shared types
3. [ ] PDA derivation uses same seeds + program ID
4. [ ] CPI `invoke_signed` uses correct signer seeds
5. [ ] Error codes map to IDL `errors`
6. [ ] Events decode from program logs per IDL
